<h1><span id="Carr_Defense">Carr Defense</span></h1>
<h3><span id="1...h6">1...h6</span></h3>
<p>A mirrored St. George Defense, this defense is considered a very weak response to the King's Pawn Opening, as not only does it not open any lines for development and allow White quick and easy development, it additionally weakens Black's king position slightly and is a time wasting move. Black often follows up with g5, Bg7, d6, and Bg4 or Bf5. Generally, Black castles queenside in the Carr Defense.
</p>
